                        <h3 class="mb-2">Faith in Action – Serving with Love and Integrity</h3>
                        <p>At the heart of our Christian life lies the belief that faith is not simply something we profess, but something we must actively live out. St. Ignatius of Loyola, taught us that we are called to be “contemplatives in action.” This concept encourages us to balance prayer and reflection with a commitment to serve others. To be contemplative in action means that while we take time to connect with God through prayer, reflection, and spiritual practices, we also understand that our faith calls us to go out into the world and make a difference.</p>
                        <p>St. Ignatius’ vision was clear: true contemplation leads us to action. As we deepen our relationship with God through prayer, we discern His will for our lives and are then led to act in ways that serve and love others. Faith in action is not a passive experience; it is an active one that demands we work for justice, help those in need, and reflect God’s love through our every action.</p>
