                        <h3 class="mb-2">Learn, Love, and Serve </h3>
                        <p>As St. Al’s Community, we are called to be contemplatives in action. This means we must live out our school motto Learn, Love, and Serve not just as a set of ideals, but as guiding principles for our daily lives. When we learn, we are called to grow in wisdom and understanding; when we love, we are called to act with compassion and empathy; and when we serve, we are called to embody the very essence of our faith, using our talents and resources for the good of others.</p>
                        <p>True service is rooted in love, and no one exemplified this more than St. Ignatius of Loyola. He taught that love, when truly felt, compels us to act. For Ignatius, love was not a passive emotion but an active force that led to service and sacrifice for the good of others. In his Spiritual Exercises, Ignatius taught that every action we take should be driven by a deep love for God and neighbor.</p>
                    </div>
