                          <p>On this St. Al’s Day, we must also acknowledge the tremendous generosity of the School of Hope Foundation. Their unwavering support has been instrumental in helping St. Al’s continue its mission of providing quality education to students in need. The generosity of the School of Hope Foundation is a true reflection of the values we hold dear—learning, loving, and serving—as they have not only provided financial support but have also invested in the future of our students and the broader community.</p>
                        <p>Through their contributions, we are able to expand our resources, improve our facilities, and offer scholarships to students who may not have had access to education otherwise. Their generosity is a reminder that love in action has the power to change lives, and we are deeply grateful for their ongoing support.</p><p>
In the spirit of Learn, Love, and Serve, it is vital that we honor the trust and generosity of our donors with integrity. At CLC Kenya, we pledge to be transparent and responsible stewards of every donation we receive. The donations we receive will be directed towards improving our school’s operations, enhancing the educational experience of our students, and ensuring that we can continue to offer the best possible environment for learning and growth.</p><p>
We understand the responsibility we bear in managing these resources, and we are committed to using them in alignment with the values of our school. Integrity is not just about being honest; it is about being responsible in how we use the resources entrusted to us. By ensuring every donation is used effectively and responsibly, we honor the generosity of our donors and continue to live out the school’s motto of Learn, Love, and Serve.</p><p>
Let us recommit ourselves to the values of Faith in Action – Serving with Love and Integrity. Inspired by St. Ignatius of Loyola, let us live as contemplatives in action—praying, reflecting, and then acting in service to others. Let us remember that in learning, we grow in wisdom; in loving, we serve with compassion; and in serving, we live out our faith in the world.
Let us be reminded that every action, no matter how small, is an opportunity to live the values of our school motto: Learn, Love, and Serve. Together, we can continue to build a community rooted in faith, love, and integrity—transforming lives and making a lasting difference in our world.
